SessionMapObject storing all the context for the lifetime of the session.

Constructor -
When a new sessionMapObject is created, a unique session_id is generated.
This session_id is used throughout the lifecycle of the session.

store:commentOut -
Ensure the mappings are stored at a (session_id, file_name, attached_identifier) => comment block

store:compactBlocks -
And the storage of mapping {f1: processCustomerOrderWithValidation, O: Order, ...} is delegated to the
sessionStore module for each of the methods, class names, packages and other relevant ones.
This mapping should be at the (project_id, block_identifier) level which can return the mapped name. 
For the prime reason being, method names, class names, packages and other class names can be uniquely identified at a project repo level.
And two different projects can have the same class names, method names. So this is a good differentiator.

get:commentOut(session_id, file_name, attached_identifier)
returns the comment block

get:compactBlockId(project_id, block_identifier)
returns the corresponding name for a given block identifier